BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan 18 May (SNARK)--Border trade between Armenia 
and Iran will begin since June 11. 
  The Armenian President's Press-Service told SNARK such 
agreement had been reached during a meeting between 
representatives of two states. 
  There were also discussed questions of simplifying the 
border 
crossing regime, intensifying the building of the bridge over 
Araks border river and regulation of the customs problems. 
  The head of the Armenian delegation Gagik Garutunyan got 
acquainted with the course of the bridge's building and viewed 
the place, intended for the border trade. 

